  include a tiredness severity scale with safety warnings, detection for COMISA
  and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, weighted EDS scoring, expanded CSV export,
  and new questions for pain and chronic fatigue symptoms.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to a detailed specification and
  SOW. The agent performed an in-depth analysis, identifying several critical
  missing features. Subsequently, the agent systematically implemented these
  features, starting with a 1-10 tiredness severity scale that triggers safety
  warnings for high scores. Other significant additions included advanced
  detection logic for complex sleep disorders like COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and
  Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, each accompanied by tailored
  recommendations. The agent also integrated weighted scoring for Excessive
  Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) and expanded the CSV export functionality to include
  all questionnaire data. Furthermore, new questions were added to screen for
  pain severity and chronic fatigue symptoms, with corresponding report
  insights. Finally, the data model was extended to capture medical and mental
  health history. The implementation involved consistent updates across data
  types, validation schemas, UI components, and both web and PDF report
  generation, ensuring a robust and feature-complete application.
